    $h = 10\sqrt{3} + 30$
    Using $\sqrt{3}=1.73205$ (rounded to five decimal places), the value of $h$ can be obtained as follows:
    $h = 10\cdot 1.73205 + 30$
    $h = 0.1723 + 30 = 30.1723 \text{ cm}$
    To three decimal places, the height of the pile is 30.172 cm

